title: Adaptive Learning in Human-AI Systems: A Multi-Agent Approach
abstract: This paper introduces a novel framework for adaptive learning in human-AI collaborative systems. We demonstrate improved robustness and fairness across diverse deployment scenarios.

title: Privacy-Preserving Federated Learning for Healthcare Applications
abstract: We present a new approach to federated learning that maintains privacy while achieving state-of-the-art performance on healthcare tasks.

title: Interactive Model Calibration with Human Feedback
abstract: A novel interface for interactive model calibration that allows domain experts to provide feedback and improve model performance.

title: Fair and Robust Deep Learning: A Comprehensive Study
abstract: An extensive analysis of fairness and robustness in deep learning systems, with practical recommendations for deployment.

title: Understanding User Trust in AI Systems
abstract: A large-scale user study examining factors that influence trust in AI systems across different application domains.

title: Efficient Training of Large Language Models with Adaptive Methods
abstract: Novel optimization techniques for training large language models that reduce computational requirements while maintaining performance.
